  "text": "To work in the Graphic Design and Visual Communication area one needs to have knowledge of different techniques and how to manipulate them. Despite the knowledge in this professional circle, there is a gap in knowledge of Colour and Inclusive Design. The interpretation of visual information, as well as semiotics is closer to meaning interpretation, is consequently highly subjective and projective. Gibson [CITATION_1] affirms that visual perception is \"richer and more open to personal interpretation\".",
